    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2218090/extras/78029409eb654650d23b281fd02b2d30.poster.avif?t=1738487145\" width=496 height=278 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2218090/extras/78029409eb654650d23b281fd02b2d30.webm?t=1738487145\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2218090/extras/78029409eb654650d23b281fd02b2d30.mp4?t=1738487145\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >THE NIGHT IS FINALLY HERE</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Every early December another kid from your school goes missing, and rumors on the playground have circulated that it's related to Krampusnacht- the night that a half-goat half-demon named Krampus comes and steals away naughty children and spares the good. <strong>But what is it that determines if people are taken by Krampus?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>For Goodness Sake</strong> is a very <strong>short horror text heavy game</strong>, focusing on several trolley problem situations. While completing the chores around the house, you find yourself reflecting on situations involving the neighborhood kids that have gone missing &amp; ultimately deciding what you think might have been the right thing to do. <strong>Will you be taken by Krampus at the end of the night like the others, or will you be spared?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Playtime: 15-20 minutes.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > 3D first person navigation</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Ending depends on your answers given</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Rich audio design and unsettling atmosphere</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Created in one month, for the HauntedPS1 community's Madvent [3] Calendar project.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2218090/extras/bf3ad1a5544c99d4b72c547228e8450c.poster.avif?t=1738487145\" width=374 height=214 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2218090/extras/bf3ad1a5544c99d4b72c547228e8450c.webm?t=1738487145\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2218090/extras/bf3ad1a5544c99d4b72c547228e8450c.mp4?t=1738487145\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This was created as a small mental break from <strong>DEAD LETTER DEPT</strong>, a psychological horror typing game also available on Steam.</p>",
